==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|wilcuma}}, meaning literally “[[well]] + [[come]]” (“May you have fared well in coming here!”). Cognate to German {{term|willkommen}}, Middle High German {{term|willekomen}},  Old High German {{term|willechomen}}, Dutch {{term|welkom}}, Danish and Norwegian {{term|velkommen}}, Swedish {{term|välkommen}}.  Similar constructions are common in [[Romance languages]], such as Spanish {{term|bienvenido}} and French {{term|bienvenue}}, each also meaning “[may you have fared] well [in] coming [here]”

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈwɛl.kəm/}}, {{SAMPA|/"welk@m/}}
* {{audio|en-us-welcome.ogg|Audio (US)}}

